  "title": "Maintenance Service Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>As Maintenance Service Engineer, you will collaborate with a multidisciplinary team of software, mechanical, electrical & electronics, and systems engineers and managers to support the Ops & Support (O&S) project. Your role includes maintaining operational systems and equipment and providing on-site engineering support.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Perform routine preventive and corrective maintenance following detailed maintenance instructions and procedures to ensure system reliability</li><li>Diagnose faults in operational systems and provide actionable recommendations to System Lead, Team Lead, or Service Managers for corrective or remedial actions</li><li>Support System Lead, Team Lead, and Service Managers in achieving SLA and KPI targets aligned with maintenance contractual agreements</li><li>Participate as on-site engineer during sea trials to support equipment deployment and validate system performance</li><li>Deliver training sessions to clients on system and hardware integration procedures, implementation, and usage to enhance client operational capability</li><li>Assist System Lead and Team Lead in installation, checkout, integration, and testing (ICIT) activities for assigned projects to ensure successful system commissioning</li><li>Communicate and coordinate effectively with internal teams and external stakeholders to facilitate smooth project execution in a dynamic work environment</li><li>Liaise with Procurement and equipment vendors to support timely acquisition and maintenance of necessary materials and tools</li><li>Travel to multiple sites within Singapore to perform maintenance and support activities as required</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electronics, Electrical, Mechatronics Engineering, or equivalent discipline with minimum of 3-4 Years related experience. </li><li>Ability to perform duties effectively in outdoor environments</li><li>Prior experience in system-level maintenance, preferably with communications systems</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in an engineering-related field</li><li>Possession of Workplace Safety and Health (WSH) certifications for workshop operations, such as Work-at-Height and Forklift Operator</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office applications (Word, PowerPoint, Excel) to document maintenance activities and prepare reports</li><li>Effective written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills to collaborate with teams and clients</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
